DPRK Anniversaries to Be Commemorated in Australia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- The Australian preparatory committee for commemorating the Day of the Sun and Feb. 16 was inaugurated in Brisbane on Feb. 1.
 The co-chairman of the Oceanic Solidarity Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of Korea was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee set a commemoration period from Feb. 1 to Apr. 20 and decided to organize political and cultural events including meeting, film show, photo exhibition and art exhibition in the period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also decided to issue an information bulletin for introducing the brilliant revolutionary history of the great persons of Mt. Paektu and their undying exploits and conduct a campaign for supporting the Korean people in their struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea.

February Holiday Marked in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- A film show was held by the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK, a film show and a photo exhibition by a Singaporean shipping company, a lecture by the Secretariat of the National Movement of Uganda and round-table talks by the Kampala City Committee of the National Movement of Uganda in the period from Jan. 24 to 27 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 Korean films including "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Pays Official Visit to the Russian Federation" were screened at film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Russian Association said that leader Kim Jong Il paid an official visit to Russia and adopted the Russia-DPRK Moscow Declaration with President Putin, adding that this marked a landmark event in the development of the relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the will of his association to make a positive contribution to developing the friendly relations between the two countries in the future, too.
 The participants of the round-table talks held by the Kampala City Committee of the National Movement of Uganda stressed that Korean-style socialism under which the warm love of Kim Jong Il for the people is combined with their resolution to repay it with loyalty is sure to triumph.

S. Korean Authorities' Deceptive Trick over FTA Negotiations under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- Farmers' and civic and social organizations in south Korea came out against the "government" authorities' deceptive trick over the negotiations for the south Korea-U.S. FTA on Feb. 2, according to the south Korean KBS.
 That day the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade held an "open hearing" for the purpose of calming down the farmers' resistance in the run-up to the negotiations slated to take place on Feb. 3 and deployed many agents to bar members of the above-said organizations from attending it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members, however, forced their ways into the venue of the hearing and staged a protest demanding a stop to the negotiations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their stubborn action scuttled the "open hearing". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the ministry asserted that it heard sufficient opinions from farmers at the hearing, adding it would inform the Meeting of Ministers Concerning External Economic Relations slated for that afternoon of them and go ahead with the negotiations with the U.S. as planned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Infuriated by this, the organizations held a press conference at which they blasted the deceptive trick of the ministry.

More Dynamic Struggle for Defence of Socialism Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- No people in the world value socialism and devotedly defend it as the people of the DPRK and it is the only country on our planet where socialism and people are linked with the same destiny.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in an editorial. It continues: 
 Socialism of Korean style was chosen and built by the popular masses themselves in conformity with the actual conditions of the country. It is socialism which the popular masses have become the master of everything and everything serves them. The source of the invincibility and vitality of socialism lies in the popular masses' undisputed support and trust in it and their dedication to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people consider socialism dearer than their lives. This revolutionary spirit has grown stronger in the course of their protracted and arduous struggle.
 The Korean people have covered a really rugged path to build socialism. But their faith in socialism has never shaken in face of any trend and tendency of the times. They have kept to the road of socialism despite manifold difficulties and ordeals. The defence of socialism would mean its victory but the abandonment of it would lead to death. This is the voice of faith that can be heard from the Korean people who regard socialism as their life and soul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said spirit will always remain noble for the Korean people who have to wage an arduous struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's unshakable faith and revolutionary spirit of regarding socialism as their life and soul serve as a most powerful mental weapon for smashing the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and a source of the energy to bring about a fresh upswing in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation.
 Underlying the strong patriotic enthusiasm of the Korean people to make the country richer and more prosperous and demonstrate its might to the whole world is their firm faith that Korean style socialism is best. The editorial calls on all the people to deepen their faith in socialism and hold higher the banner of socialism of Juche in order to meet the increasing challenges of the imperialists, deal resolute retaliatory blows at their moves and continue to give full play to the spirit displayed in the period of "the Arduous March".

Preparatory Work for Kimjongilia Festival at Full Swing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- The preparatory work for the 10th Kimjongilia Festival to be held on the occasion of the February holiday, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, is going on with a swing in different parts of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, the Secretariat of the Cabinet, the State Academy of Sciences and other ministries and national institutions, which had been highly appreciated at the previous festivals, are dynamically pushing ahead with the preparatory work for the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimjongilias begin to open flowers at Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia greenhouses built in Pyongyang, North Hamgyong and other provinces, cities and counties throughout the country under the special concern  and  the expectation of the people.
 Servicepersons and working people across the country are doing their best to cultivate the flower plants by regulating temperature, light and humidity in a scientific way even in the biting cold weather. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Yong Je, a department director of the Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee, told KCNA that the scale and the number of participants of the festival have increased year after year since the first Kimjongilia exhibition was held in Juche 86 (1997). 
 The number of applicants at present, he went on, is more than that of the previous festival and it is expected that the number of flower plants to be displayed will grow by thousands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival will be attended by overseas Koreans and foreigners.
 The upcoming festival will be more conspicuous in the ever-deepening interest of the people at home and abroad in the immortal flower Kimjongilia.

New High Yielding Oil-bearing Trees Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- The Economic Forest Institute under the Academy of Forestry of the Ministry of Land and Environment Conservation has developed new species of short walnut and Xanthoceras sorbifolia. They are high-yield trees of economic value.
 The newly developed walnut tree bears fruits even one year after its plantation.
 Its yield is seven times that of spontaneous walnut tree and 1.4 times that of previously cultivated walnut tree. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is expected to bear fruits for 40-50 years. Its peak years are between 15 and 20 years following its plantation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The weight and kernel per a new walnut are heavier and its nut is thinner than those of other species of walnuts. 
 It, also convenient to tend, stands well cold and diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new species of Xanthoceras sorbifolia will bear fruits for a hundred years from two or three years after its seed was sown. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ten-year-old tree bears 80-100 burs, each of which has about 18 chestnuts.
 The kernel contains large amounts of oil and protein and nearly ten percent of starch. And the weight of kernel per chestnut is 4 percent and the amount of its oil 8-10 percent higher than those of the spontaneous chestnuts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The per hectare yield of the new species of Xanthoceras sorbifolia is five or seven times that of spontaneous ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its oil contains linolic acid, oleic acid, vitamin E, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Su, head of the institute, told KCNA the institute is directing efforts to nursing their saplings in close cooperation with a relevant department of the Ministry of Agriculture in order to transplant the new species of oil-bearing trees in different places of the country in an extensive way.

S. Korean Authorities Urged to Stop All Joint Military Exercises with Outsiders
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- The south Korean authorities should unconditionally stop all the joint military exercises with outside forces which would bring dark clouds of a nuclear war if they truly desire progress in the north-south relations and peace on the Korean Peninsula.
 A spokesman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland demanded this in an answer given to a question raised by KCNA today blasting the south Korean authorities for contemplating staging with the U.S. joint military exercises under the simulated conditions of invasion against the north this year, too. 
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Feb. 1 the south Korean minister of Defence at a regular press conference blustered that all the exercises under this year's plan as well as the south Korea-U.S. joint military exercises due in upcoming March would be staged as scheduled.
 This announcement of the plan to stage the joint military exercises with the U.S. this year too, came at a time when the north-south military authorities' talks that had been arranged with much effort are just around the corner. This is a very provocative act of negating the military talks themselves and pushing the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war pursuant to the U.S. moves to start a war of aggression against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities staged with the U.S. extremely dangerous war exercises against the north in the era of the Cold War and now they intend to go ahead with those exercises even in the June 15 era of independent reunification.  This is a challenge to the desire of the nation and the trend of the times and an action against peace and reunification as it is aimed at bedeviling the inter-Korean relations and scrapping the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities called for north-south military talks before negotiators of the north, talking about "building military confidence" and "detente." But they have disclosed their intention to go on with joint military exercises against the fellow countrymen with the outsiders behind the scene. This is an intolerable mockery of the dialogue partner and an artifice to fool the public opinion. 
 The south Korean military authorities should clarify whether they stand for reconciliation and cooperation or for confrontation and war.
